<p>So, I have a DNS server running on the the local host. I want to add a service using <code>nsupdate</code> with a command file like the following:</p>  <pre><code>server localhost zone sstewartgallus.localhost. update add sstewartgallus.localhost 0 IN NAPTR 100 10 "s" "x-ssg-custom-service:file" ( "" _file._x-ssg-unix.sstewartgallus.localhost ) update add _file._x-ssg-unix.sstewartgallus.localhost 0 IN URI 0 0 "file:///myunixsocketpathhere" </code></pre>  <p>Is this the correct way of specifying custom services using URIs and NAPTR records for use only on the localhost?</p>